722682f-a.text:
(1)
16 to 33 Rector Street, north side, west from, but not including Greenwich to and including West Streets. At the extreme left, is the 17-story Barrett Building, bearing Nos. 26-33 and occupying the block from Washington to West Streets. Also shown is a portion of Pier No. 8 North River (Hudson River).
June 22, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
Neg #400

(2)
A portion of the same, showing a comprehensive view of the 2-story building Nos. 18-16 and includiag No. 12 (4-story house), at the N.W. corner of Greenwich Street. At the extreme right, is shown a portion of the Rector Street station of the Ninth Ave. Elevated Line.
June 22, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
Neg #400

720174f-a.text:
Greenwich Street (building line across foreground) at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Rector Street (extreme right, not seen ) showing at the corner the 23 story Electric Bond and Share Building (No. 2 Rector Street). To the north of same are low structures and across which appears a glimpse of the rear of Trinity Church. The photographers vantage point is the Barrett Building, No. 6O West Street and from which he is viewing due eastward towards Broadway at Wall Street. Note across the top, the portions of the Equitable, the Bankers Trust, the Bank of Manhattan and the Irving Trust Company Buildings.
July 30, 1930.
P.L. Sperr
